## Filtering Rules
1. Must match at least one role keyword (title or description)
2. Visa sponsorship: prefer jobs mentioning "visa sponsorship", "visa support", "relocation", "work permit" — flag these as priority
3. Language: accept English-language postings OR postings that mention English as working language. Do NOT filter out non-English postings if they accept English speakers.
4. Salary: if salary data is available, flag jobs BELOW the visa minimum threshold
   as low priority (still include them). Thresholds by country:
   - Germany: €45,000/year (Blue Card minimum for shortage occupations like IT)
   - France: €43,000/year
   - Canada: CAD 55,000/year
   - Ireland: €32,000/year
   If no salary data → include job normally, mark salary as "not specified"
   Do NOT hard-filter out any job based on salary alone.
5. Deduplicate by job URL — never send the same job twice

---

## Scoring (LLM-based)
Use Huawei MaaS API (OpenAI-compatible endpoint).

The base URL and API key will be provided as environment variables:
- HUAWEI_MAAS_BASE_URL
- HUAWEI_MAAS_API_KEY
- HUAWEI_MAAS_MODEL (default: "glm-4" or configurable)

Use the openai Python SDK pointed at the Huawei MaaS base URL.

For each job, send this prompt to the LLM:
"""
You are a job relevance scorer. Score this job posting for a candidate with this profile:
- Cloud presales engineer at Huawei, 3 years experience
- Skills: HCS private cloud, GaussDB, Kubernetes, solution architecture, client presentations, RFP responses
- Looking for: presales, solutions engineering, cloud architecture, or technical account management roles
- Languages: French, English, Arabic
- Requires visa sponsorship (non-EU, non-Canadian citizen)

Job title: {title}
Company: {company}
Location: {location}
Description (first 500 chars): {description[:500]}

Respond ONLY with a JSON object: {"score": <1-10>, "reason": "<one sentence>", "visa_likely": <true/false>}
"""

Only call LLM for jobs that passed keyword filtering. Cache scores in SQLite.

---

## Storage — SQLite
File: jobs.db

Table: seen_jobs
- id (TEXT PRIMARY KEY) — MD5 of job URL
- url (TEXT)
- title (TEXT)
- company (TEXT)
- location (TEXT)
- country (TEXT)
- salary (TEXT)
- score (INTEGER)
- visa_likely (BOOLEAN)
- reason (TEXT)
- source (TEXT)
- first_seen (TIMESTAMP)
- notified (BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE)

---

## Telegram Notification
Environment variables:
- TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN
- TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID

Every 6 hours, after scraping all sources:
1. Query jobs where notified=FALSE and score >= 6, ordered by score DESC
2. Send a digest message grouped by country
3. Format each job as:
🌍 GERMANY | Score: 8/10

💼 Solutions Engineer — SAP

📍 Berlin

💰 €65,000/year

🛂 Visa: Likely ✅

📝 Strong presales fit, mentions relocation support

🔗 https://...

4. Send max 15 jobs per digest to avoid spam. If more exist, say "X more jobs available, next digest in 6h"
5. Mark all sent jobs as notified=TRUE

---

## Scheduling
Use APScheduler (BackgroundScheduler). Run the full pipeline every 6 hours.
Also support a manual trigger: run with `python main.py --now` to force immediate run.

